FBIS4-29645 "dreas119_g_94002" FBIS-EAS-94-119 Daily Report 16 Jun 1994 SOUTHEAST ASIA Burma Rebel Couple Surrenders in Mergui 8 Jun Rebel Couple Surrenders in Mergui 8 Jun BK1706103594 Rangoon Radio Burma in Burmese 1330 GMT 16 Jun 94 BK1706103594 Rangoon Radio Burma Burmese BFN [Text] Members of armed groups who have come to realize their wrongdoings and, after accepting the work being undertaken and the genuine goodwill of the State Law and Order Restoration Council, have been giving up their armed struggle and surrendering with their arms and ammunition at various military camps. On 8 June, Private Hla Tun, 23, son of U Kyaw Pe, and his wife Ma Nwe Yee Win, 21, daughter of U Aung Maung, from the BCP [Burma Communist Party] armed organization surrendered together with two AK-47 assault rifles, two magazines, 20 rounds of ammunition, one BA-63 automatic rifle, and one magazine at the Pankin Camp, Mergui regional headquarters. They were warmly welcomed by responsible personnel at the concerned camp.
